---
import ChapterLayout from '../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro';
---

<ChapterLayout 
  title="My Tech Journey - Chapter II" 
  description="From first lines of code to full-stack development - the evolution of a software engineer"
  chapter="Chapter II" 
  chapterTitle="My Tech Journey" 
  chapterColor="sky"
>
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-4xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-8">
          The Evolution of a Developer
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Every developer has a unique story. Here's mine — from the first "Hello, World!" to building complex systems that serve real users.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Timeline -->
      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Timeline Line -->
        <div class="absolute left-8 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-sky-400 to-sky-600 dark:from-sky-500 dark:to-sky-700"></div>
        
        <div class="space-y-12">
          <!-- The Spark -->
          <div class="relative flex items-start">
            <div class="absolute left-4 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-sky-400 dark:bg-sky-500 border-4 border-white dark:border-ink-800 shadow-soft"></div>
            <div class="ml-16">
              <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">The Spark</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 mb-4">
                  It all started with curiosity. I was fascinated by how websites worked, how apps seemed to "know" what I wanted. The idea that I could create something from nothing, just lines of text, was intoxicating.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">HTML</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">CSS</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">JavaScript</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Hello, World! -->
          <div class="relative flex items-start">
            <div class="absolute left-4 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-sky-400 dark:bg-sky-500 border-4 border-white dark:border-ink-800 shadow-soft"></div>
            <div class="ml-16">
              <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">Hello, World!</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 mb-4">
                  My first real programming experience was with Java. The structured approach, object-oriented principles, and the feeling of building something substantial clicked with me immediately.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">Java</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">OOP</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">Data Structures</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Deep Dive -->
          <div class="relative flex items-start">
            <div class="absolute left-4 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-sky-400 dark:bg-sky-500 border-4 border-white dark:border-ink-800 shadow-soft"></div>
            <div class="ml-16">
              <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">The Deep Dive</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 mb-4">
                  University opened up a whole new world. Algorithms, databases, software engineering principles — I was building real applications, not just exercises. The complexity was challenging but exhilarating.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">Spring Boot</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">MySQL</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">REST APIs</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- First Real Project -->
          <div class="relative flex items-start">
            <div class="absolute left-4 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-sky-400 dark:bg-sky-500 border-4 border-white dark:border-ink-800 shadow-soft"></div>
            <div class="ml-16">
              <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
                <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">First Real Project</h3>
                <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 mb-4">
                  Building something that actual users would interact with was a game-changer. Suddenly, code wasn't just about functionality — it was about experience, reliability, and solving real problems.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">Full-Stack</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">React</span>
                  <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900 text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 rounded-full text-sm">User Experience</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Current State -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white dark:bg-ink-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-8">
          Where I Am Now
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-600 dark:text-ink-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Two years of hands-on experience later, I'm still learning, still growing, and still excited about what's next.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Backend Expertise -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-200 to-sky-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,2A10,10 0 0,0 2,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,22A10,10 0 0,0 22,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,2M12,4A8,8 0 0,1 20,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,20A8,8 0 0,1 4,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,4M12,6A6,6 0 0,0 6,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,18A6,6 0 0,0 18,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,6M12,8A4,4 0 0,1 16,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,16A4,4 0 0,1 8,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,8Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">Backend Expertise</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 text-sm">
            Java, Spring Boot, microservices architecture, and database design. Building robust, scalable systems that handle real-world loads.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Frontend Skills -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-200 to-sky-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,2A10,10 0 0,0 2,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,22A10,10 0 0,0 22,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,2M12,4A8,8 0 0,1 20,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,20A8,8 0 0,1 4,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,4M12,6A6,6 0 0,0 6,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,18A6,6 0 0,0 18,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,6M12,8A4,4 0 0,1 16,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,16A4,4 0 0,1 8,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,8Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">Frontend Skills</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 text-sm">
            React, TypeScript, modern CSS frameworks. Creating intuitive, responsive interfaces that users love to interact with.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- DevOps & Cloud -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-sky-50 dark:from-ink-800 dark:to-ink-700 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-soft">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-200 to-sky-400 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M12,2A10,10 0 0,0 2,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,22A10,10 0 0,0 22,12A10,10 0 0,0 12,2M12,4A8,8 0 0,1 20,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,20A8,8 0 0,1 4,12A8,8 0 0,1 12,4M12,6A6,6 0 0,0 6,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,18A6,6 0 0,0 18,12A6,6 0 0,0 12,6M12,8A4,4 0 0,1 16,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,16A4,4 0 0,1 8,12A4,4 0 0,1 12,8Z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-3">DevOps & Cloud</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 text-sm">
            Docker, AWS, CI/CD pipelines. Understanding the full deployment lifecycle and cloud-native development practices.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Call to Action -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-100 to-mint-100 dark:from-sky-900/20 dark:to-mint-900/20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-ink-800 dark:text-ink-100 mb-6">
        Ready to See What I Can Build?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Now that you know my journey, let's explore the tools and technologies I use to bring ideas to life.
      </p>
      <a href="/toolkit" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-500 to-mint-500 text-white font-medium hover:shadow-chapter transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105">
        <span>Explore My Toolkit</span>
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</ChapterLayout> 